name: Getting updates
description:
There are two mutually exclusive ways of receiving updates for your bot - the getUpdates method on one hand and webhooks on the other. Incoming updates are stored on the server until the bot receives them either way, but they will not be kept longer than 24 hours.

Regardless of which option you choose, you will receive JSON-serialized Update objects as a result.

docTypes.name: Update
docTypes.description:
This object represents an incoming update.
At most one of the optional parameters can be present in any given update.

docFields.name: update_id
docFields.description: The update's unique identifier. Update identifiers start from a certain positive number and increase sequentially. This identifier becomes especially handy if you're using webhooks, since it allows you to ignore repeated updates or to restore the correct update sequence, should they get out of order. If there are no new updates for at least a week, then identifier of the next update will be chosen randomly instead of sequentially.

docFields.name: message
docFields.description: Optional. New incoming message of any kind - text, photo, sticker, etc.

docFields.name: edited_message
docFields.description: Optional. New version of a message that is known to the bot and was edited. This update may at times be triggered by changes to message fields that are either unavailable or not actively used by your bot.

docFields.name: channel_post
docFields.description: Optional. New incoming channel post of any kind - text, photo, sticker, etc.

docFields.name: edited_channel_post
docFields.description: Optional. New version of a channel post that is known to the bot and was edited. This update may at times be triggered by changes to message fields that are either unavailable or not actively used by your bot.

docFields.name: business_connection
docFields.description: Optional. The bot was connected to or disconnected from a business account, or a user edited an existing connection with the bot

docFields.name: business_message
docFields.description: Optional. New message from a connected business account

docFields.name: edited_business_message
docFields.description: Optional. New version of a message from a connected business account

docFields.name: deleted_business_messages
docFields.description: Optional. Messages were deleted from a connected business account

docFields.name: message_reaction
docFields.description: Optional. A reaction to a message was changed by a user. The bot must be an administrator in the chat and must explicitly specify "message_reaction" in the list of allowed_updates to receive these updates. The update isn't received for reactions set by bots.

docFields.name: message_reaction_count
docFields.description: Optional. Reactions to a message with anonymous reactions were changed. The bot must be an administrator in the chat and must explicitly specify "message_reaction_count" in the list of allowed_updates to receive these updates. The updates are grouped and can be sent with delay up to a few minutes.

docFields.name: inline_query
docFields.description: Optional. New incoming inline query

docFields.name: chosen_inline_result
docFields.description: Optional. The result of an inline query that was chosen by a user and sent to their chat partner. Please see our documentation on the feedback collecting for details on how to enable these updates for your bot.

docFields.name: callback_query
docFields.description: Optional. New incoming callback query

docFields.name: shipping_query
docFields.description: Optional. New incoming shipping query. Only for invoices with flexible price

docFields.name: pre_checkout_query
docFields.description: Optional. New incoming pre-checkout query. Contains full information about checkout

docFields.name: poll
docFields.description: Optional. New poll state. Bots receive only updates about manually stopped polls and polls, which are sent by the bot

docFields.name: poll_answer
docFields.description: Optional. A user changed their answer in a non-anonymous poll. Bots receive new votes only in polls that were sent by the bot itself.

docFields.name: my_chat_member
docFields.description: Optional. The bot's chat member status was updated in a chat. For private chats, this update is received only when the bot is blocked or unblocked by the user.

docFields.name: chat_member
docFields.description: Optional. A chat member's status was updated in a chat. The bot must be an administrator in the chat and must explicitly specify "chat_member" in the list of allowed_updates to receive these updates.

docFields.name: chat_join_request
docFields.description: Optional. A request to join the chat has been sent. The bot must have the can_invite_users administrator right in the chat to receive these updates.

docFields.name: chat_boost
docFields.description: Optional. A chat boost was added or changed. The bot must be an administrator in the chat to receive these updates.

docFields.name: removed_chat_boost
docFields.description: Optional. A boost was removed from a chat. The bot must be an administrator in the chat to receive these updates.

docTypes.name: WebhookInfo
docTypes.description: Describes the current status of a webhook.

docFields.name: url
docFields.description: Webhook URL, may be empty if webhook is not set up

docFields.name: has_custom_certificate
docFields.description: True, if a custom certificate was provided for webhook certificate checks

docFields.name: pending_update_count
docFields.description: Number of updates awaiting delivery

docFields.name: ip_address
docFields.description: Optional. Currently used webhook IP address

docFields.name: last_error_date
docFields.description: Optional. Unix time for the most recent error that happened when trying to deliver an update via webhook

docFields.name: last_error_message
docFields.description: Optional. Error message in human-readable format for the most recent error that happened when trying to deliver an update via webhook

docFields.name: last_synchronization_error_date
docFields.description: Optional. Unix time of the most recent error that happened when trying to synchronize available updates with Telegram datacenters

docFields.name: max_connections
docFields.description: Optional. The maximum allowed number of simultaneous HTTPS connections to the webhook for update delivery

docFields.name: allowed_updates
docFields.description: Optional. A list of update types the bot is subscribed to. Defaults to all update types except chat_member

docMethods.name: getUpdates
docMethods.description:
Use this method to receive incoming updates using long polling (wiki). Returns an Array of Update objects.

Notes
1. This method will not work if an outgoing webhook is set up.
2. In order to avoid getting duplicate updates, recalculate offset after each server response.

docParameters.name: offset
docParameters.description: Identifier of the first update to be returned. Must be greater by one than the highest among the identifiers of previously received updates. By default, updates starting with the earliest unconfirmed update are returned. An update is considered confirmed as soon as getUpdates is called with an offset higher than its update_id. The negative offset can be specified to retrieve updates starting from -offset update from the end of the updates queue. All previous updates will be forgotten.

docParameters.name: limit
docParameters.description: Limits the number of updates to be retrieved. Values between 1-100 are accepted. Defaults to 100.

docParameters.name: timeout
docParameters.description: Timeout in seconds for long polling. Defaults to 0, i.e. usual short polling. Should be positive, short polling should be used for testing purposes only.

docParameters.name: allowed_updates
docParameters.description:
A JSON-serialized list of the update types you want your bot to receive. For example, specify ["message", "edited_channel_post", "callback_query"] to only receive updates of these types. See Update for a complete list of available update types. Specify an empty list to receive all update types except chat_member, message_reaction, and message_reaction_count (default). If not specified, the previous setting will be used.

Please note that this parameter doesn't affect updates created before the call to the getUpdates, so unwanted updates may be received for a short period of time.

docParametersSorded.name: offset
docParametersSorded.description: Identifier of the first update to be returned. Must be greater by one than the highest among the identifiers of previously received updates. By default, updates starting with the earliest unconfirmed update are returned. An update is considered confirmed as soon as getUpdates is called with an offset higher than its update_id. The negative offset can be specified to retrieve updates starting from -offset update from the end of the updates queue. All previous updates will be forgotten.

docParametersSorded.name: limit
docParametersSorded.description: Limits the number of updates to be retrieved. Values between 1-100 are accepted. Defaults to 100.

docParametersSorded.name: timeout
docParametersSorded.description: Timeout in seconds for long polling. Defaults to 0, i.e. usual short polling. Should be positive, short polling should be used for testing purposes only.

docParametersSorded.name: allowed_updates
docParametersSorded.description:
A JSON-serialized list of the update types you want your bot to receive. For example, specify ["message", "edited_channel_post", "callback_query"] to only receive updates of these types. See Update for a complete list of available update types. Specify an empty list to receive all update types except chat_member, message_reaction, and message_reaction_count (default). If not specified, the previous setting will be used.

Please note that this parameter doesn't affect updates created before the call to the getUpdates, so unwanted updates may be received for a short period of time.

docMethods.name: setWebhook
docMethods.description:
Use this method to specify a URL and receive incoming updates via an outgoing webhook. Whenever there is an update for the bot, we will send an HTTPS POST request to the specified URL, containing a JSON-serialized Update. In case of an unsuccessful request, we will give up after a reasonable amount of attempts. Returns True on success.

If you'd like to make sure that the webhook was set by you, you can specify secret data in the parameter secret_token. If specified, the request will contain a header “X-Telegram-Bot-Api-Secret-Token” with the secret token as content.

Notes
1. You will not be able to receive updates using getUpdates for as long as an outgoing webhook is set up.
2. To use a self-signed certificate, you need to upload your public key certificate using certificate parameter. Please upload as InputFile, sending a String will not work.
3. Ports currently supported for webhooks: 443, 80, 88, 8443.

If you're having any trouble setting up webhooks, please check out this amazing guide to webhooks.

docParameters.name: url
docParameters.description: HTTPS URL to send updates to. Use an empty string to remove webhook integration

docParameters.name: certificate
docParameters.description: Upload your public key certificate so that the root certificate in use can be checked. See our self-signed guide for details.

docParameters.name: ip_address
docParameters.description: The fixed IP address which will be used to send webhook requests instead of the IP address resolved through DNS

docParameters.name: max_connections
docParameters.description: The maximum allowed number of simultaneous HTTPS connections to the webhook for update delivery, 1-100. Defaults to 40. Use lower values to limit the load on your bot's server, and higher values to increase your bot's throughput.

docParameters.name: allowed_updates
docParameters.description:
A JSON-serialized list of the update types you want your bot to receive. For example, specify ["message", "edited_channel_post", "callback_query"] to only receive updates of these types. See Update for a complete list of available update types. Specify an empty list to receive all update types except chat_member, message_reaction, and message_reaction_count (default). If not specified, the previous setting will be used.
Please note that this parameter doesn't affect updates created before the call to the setWebhook, so unwanted updates may be received for a short period of time.

docParameters.name: drop_pending_updates
docParameters.description: Pass True to drop all pending updates

docParameters.name: secret_token
docParameters.description: A secret token to be sent in a header “X-Telegram-Bot-Api-Secret-Token” in every webhook request, 1-256 characters. Only characters A-Z, a-z, 0-9, _ and - are allowed. The header is useful to ensure that the request comes from a webhook set by you.

docParameters.name: invalid_user_url
docParameters.description: HTTPS URL to send updates to. Use an empty string to remove webhook integration

docParametersSorded.name: url
docParametersSorded.description: HTTPS URL to send updates to. Use an empty string to remove webhook integration

docParametersSorded.name: certificate
docParametersSorded.description: Upload your public key certificate so that the root certificate in use can be checked. See our self-signed guide for details.

docParametersSorded.name: ip_address

docParametersSorded.name: max_connections

See Update for a complete list of available update types. Specify an empty list to receive all update types except chat_member, message_reaction, and message_reaction_count (default). If not specified, the previous setting will be used.
Please note that this parameter doesn't affect updates created before the call to the setWebhook, so unwanted updates may be received for a short period of time.

docParametersSorded.name: drop_pending_updates
docParametersSorded.description: Pass True to drop all pending updates

docParametersSorded.name: secret_token
docParametersSorded.description: A secret token to be sent in a header “X-Telegram-Bot-Api-Secret-Token” in every webhook request, 1-256 characters. Only characters A-Z, a-z, 0-9, _ and - are allowed. The header is useful to ensure that the request comes from a webhook set by you.

docParametersSorded.name: invalid_user_url
docParametersSorded.description: HTTPS URL to send updates to. Use an empty string to remove webhook integration

docMethods.name: deleteWebhook
docMethods.description: Use this method to remove webhook integration if you decide to switch back to getUpdates. Returns True on success.

docParameters.name: drop_pending_updates
docParameters.description: Pass True to drop all pending updates

docParametersSorded.name: drop_pending_updates
docParametersSorded.description: Pass True to drop all pending updates

docMethods.name: getWebhookInfo
docMethods.description: Use this method to get current webhook status. Requires no parameters. On success, returns a WebhookInfo object. If the bot is using getUpdates, will return an object with the url field empty.

name: Available types
description:
All types used in the Bot API responses are represented as JSON-objects.

It is safe to use 32-bit signed integers for storing all Integer fields unless otherwise noted.

Optional fields may be not returned when irrelevant.

docTypes.name: User
docTypes.description: This object represents a Telegram user or bot.

docFields.name: id
docFields.description: Unique identifier for this user or bot. This number may have more than 32 significant bits and some programming languages may have difficulty/silent defects in interpreting it. But it has at most 52 significant bits, so a 64-bit integer or double-precision float type are safe for storing this identifier.

docFields.name: is_bot
docFields.description: True, if this user is a bot

docFields.name: first_name
docFields.description: User's or bot's first name

docFields.name: last_name
docFields.description: Optional. User's or bot's last name

docFields.name: username
docFields.description: Optional. User's or bot's username

docFields.name: language_code
docFields.description: Optional. IETF language tag of the user's language

docFields.name: is_premium
docFields.description: Optional. True, if this user is a Telegram Premium user

docFields.name: added_to_attachment_menu
docFields.description: Optional. True, if this user added the bot to the attachment menu

docFields.name: can_join_groups
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the bot can be invited to groups. Returned only in getMe.

docFields.name: can_read_all_group_messages
docFields.description: Optional. True, if privacy mode is disabled for the bot. Returned only in getMe.

docFields.name: supports_inline_queries
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the bot supports inline queries. Returned only in getMe.

docFields.name: can_connect_to_business
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the bot can be connected to a Telegram Business account to receive its messages. Returned only in getMe.

docTypes.name: Chat
docTypes.description: This object represents a chat.

docFields.name: id
docFields.description: Unique identifier for this chat. This number may have more than 32 significant bits and some programming languages may have difficulty/silent defects in interpreting it. But it has at most 52 significant bits, so a signed 64-bit integer or double-precision float type are safe for storing this identifier.

docFields.name: type
docFields.description: Type of the chat, can be either “private”, “group”, “supergroup” or “channel”

docFields.name: title
docFields.description: Optional. Title, for supergroups, channels and group chats

docFields.name: username
docFields.description: Optional. Username, for private chats, supergroups and channels if available

docFields.name: first_name
docFields.description: Optional. First name of the other party in a private chat

docFields.name: last_name
docFields.description: Optional. Last name of the other party in a private chat

docFields.name: is_forum
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the supergroup chat is a forum (has topics enabled)

docTypes.name: ChatFullInfo
docTypes.description: This object contains full information about a chat.

docFields.name: id
docFields.description: Unique identifier for this chat. This number may have more than 32 significant bits and some programming languages may have difficulty/silent defects in interpreting it. But it has at most 52 significant bits, so a signed 64-bit integer or double-precision float type are safe for storing this identifier.

docFields.name: type
docFields.description: Type of the chat, can be either “private”, “group”, “supergroup” or “channel”

docFields.name: title
docFields.description: Optional. Title, for supergroups, channels and group chats

docFields.name: username
docFields.description: Optional. Username, for private chats, supergroups and channels if available

docFields.name: first_name
docFields.description: Optional. First name of the other party in a private chat

docFields.name: last_name
docFields.description: Optional. Last name of the other party in a private chat

docFields.name: is_forum
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the supergroup chat is a forum (has topics enabled)

docFields.name: accent_color_id
docFields.description: Identifier of the accent color for the chat name and backgrounds of the chat photo, reply header, and link preview. See accent colors for more details.

docFields.name: max_reaction_count
docFields.description: The maximum number of reactions that can be set on a message in the chat

docFields.name: photo
docFields.description: Optional. Chat photo

docFields.name: active_usernames
docFields.description: Optional. If non-empty, the list of all active chat usernames; for private chats, supergroups and channels

docFields.name: birthdate
docFields.description: Optional. For private chats, the date of birth of the user

docFields.name: business_intro
docFields.description: Optional. For private chats with business accounts, the intro of the business

docFields.name: business_location
docFields.description: Optional. For private chats with business accounts, the location of the business

docFields.name: business_opening_hours
docFields.description: Optional. For private chats with business accounts, the opening hours of the business

docFields.name: personal_chat
docFields.description: Optional. For private chats, the personal channel of the user

docFields.name: available_reactions
docFields.description: Optional. List of available reactions allowed in the chat. If omitted, then all emoji reactions are allowed.

docFields.name: background_custom_emoji_id
docFields.description: Optional. Custom emoji identifier of the emoji chosen by the chat for the reply header and link preview background

docFields.name: profile_accent_color_id
docFields.description: Optional. Identifier of the accent color for the chat's profile background. See profile accent colors for more details.

docFields.name: profile_background_custom_emoji_id
docFields.description: Optional. Custom emoji identifier of the emoji chosen by the chat for its profile background

docFields.name: emoji_status_custom_emoji_id
docFields.description: Optional. Custom emoji identifier of the emoji status of the chat or the other party in a private chat

docFields.name: emoji_status_expiration_date
docFields.description: Optional. Expiration date of the emoji status of the chat or the other party in a private chat, in Unix time, if any

docFields.name: bio
docFields.description: Optional. Bio of the other party in a private chat

docFields.name: has_private_forwards
docFields.description: Optional. True, if privacy settings of the other party in the private chat allows to use tg://user?id=<user_id> links only in chats with the user

docFields.name: has_restricted_voice_and_video_messages
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the privacy settings of the other party restrict sending voice and video note messages in the private chat

docFields.name: join_to_send_messages
docFields.description: Optional. True, if users need to join the supergroup before they can send messages

docFields.name: join_by_request
docFields.description: Optional. True, if all users directly joining the supergroup without using an invite link need to be approved by supergroup administrators

docFields.name: description
docFields.description: Optional. Description, for groups, supergroups and channel chats

docFields.name: invite_link
docFields.description: Optional. Primary invite link, for groups, supergroups and channel chats

docFields.name: pinned_message
docFields.description: Optional. The most recent pinned message (by sending date)

docFields.name: permissions
docFields.description: Optional. Default chat member permissions, for groups and supergroups

docFields.name: slow_mode_delay
docFields.description: Optional. For supergroups, the minimum allowed delay between consecutive messages sent by each unprivileged user; in seconds

docFields.name: unrestrict_boost_count
docFields.description: Optional. For supergroups, the minimum number of boosts that a non-administrator user needs to add in order to ignore slow mode and chat permissions

docFields.name: message_auto_delete_time
docFields.description: Optional. The time after which all messages sent to the chat will be automatically deleted; in seconds

docFields.name: has_aggressive_anti_spam_enabled
docFields.description: Optional. True, if aggressive anti-spam checks are enabled in the supergroup. The field is only available to chat administrators.

docFields.name: has_hidden_members
docFields.description: Optional. True, if non-administrators can only get the list of bots and administrators in the chat

docFields.name: has_protected_content
docFields.description: Optional. True, if messages from the chat can't be forwarded to other chats

docFields.name: has_visible_history
docFields.description: Optional. True, if new chat members will have access to old messages; available only to chat administrators

docFields.name: sticker_set_name
docFields.description: Optional. For supergroups, name of the group sticker set

docFields.name: can_set_sticker_set
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the bot can change the group sticker set

docFields.name: custom_emoji_sticker_set_name
docFields.description: Optional. For supergroups, the name of the group's custom emoji sticker set. Custom emoji from this set can be used by all users and bots in the group.

docFields.name: linked_chat_id
docFields.description: Optional. Unique identifier for the linked chat, i.e. the discussion group identifier for a channel and vice versa; for supergroups and channel chats. This identifier may be greater than 32 bits and some programming languages may have difficulty/silent defects in interpreting it. But it is smaller than 52 bits, so a signed 64 bit integer or double-precision float type are safe for storing this identifier.

docFields.name: location
docFields.description: Optional. For supergroups, the location to which the supergroup is connected

docTypes.name: Message
docTypes.description: This object represents a message.

docFields.name: message_id
docFields.description: Unique message identifier inside this chat

docFields.name: message_thread_id
docFields.description: Optional. Unique identifier of a message thread to which the message belongs; for supergroups only

docFields.name: from
docFields.description: Optional. Sender of the message; empty for messages sent to channels. For backward compatibility, the field contains a fake sender user in non-channel chats, if the message was sent on behalf of a chat.

docFields.name: sender_chat
docFields.description: Optional. Sender of the message, sent on behalf of a chat. For example, the channel itself for channel posts, the supergroup itself for messages from anonymous group administrators, the linked channel for messages automatically forwarded to the discussion group. For backward compatibility, the field from contains a fake sender user in non-channel chats, if the message was sent on behalf of a chat.

docFields.name: sender_boost_count
docFields.description: Optional. If the sender of the message boosted the chat, the number of boosts added by the user

docFields.name: sender_business_bot
docFields.description: Optional. The bot that actually sent the message on behalf of the business account. Available only for outgoing messages sent on behalf of the connected business account.

docFields.name: date
docFields.description: Date the message was sent in Unix time. It is always a positive number, representing a valid date.

docFields.name: business_connection_id
docFields.description: Optional. Unique identifier of the business connection from which the message was received. If non-empty, the message belongs to a chat of the corresponding business account that is independent from any potential bot chat which might share the same identifier.

docFields.name: chat
docFields.description: Chat the message belongs to

docFields.name: forward_origin
docFields.description: Optional. Information about the original message for forwarded messages

docFields.name: is_topic_message
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the message is sent to a forum topic

docFields.name: is_automatic_forward
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the message is a channel post that was automatically forwarded to the connected discussion group

docFields.name: reply_to_message
docFields.description: Optional. For replies in the same chat and message thread, the original message. Note that the Message object in this field will not contain further reply_to_message fields even if it itself is a reply.

docFields.name: external_reply
docFields.description: Optional. Information about the message that is being replied to, which may come from another chat or forum topic

docFields.name: quote
docFields.description: Optional. For replies that quote part of the original message, the quoted part of the message

docFields.name: reply_to_story
docFields.description: Optional. For replies to a story, the original story

docFields.name: via_bot
docFields.description: Optional. Bot through which the message was sent

docFields.name: edit_date
docFields.description: Optional. Date the message was last edited in Unix time

docFields.name: has_protected_content
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the message can't be forwarded

docFields.name: is_from_offline
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the message was sent by an implicit action, for example, as an away or a greeting business message, or as a scheduled message

docFields.name: media_group_id
docFields.description: Optional. The unique identifier of a media message group this message belongs to

docFields.name: author_signature
docFields.description: Optional. Signature of the post author for messages in channels, or the custom title of an anonymous group administrator

docFields.name: text
docFields.description: Optional. For text messages, the actual UTF-8 text of the message

docFields.name: entities
docFields.description: Optional. For text messages, special entities like usernames, URLs, bot commands, etc. that appear in the text

docFields.name: link_preview_options
docFields.description: Optional. Options used for link preview generation for the message, if it is a text message and link preview options were changed

docFields.name: effect_id
docFields.description: Optional. Unique identifier of the message effect added to the message

docFields.name: animation
docFields.description: Optional. Message is an animation, information about the animation. For backward compatibility, when this field is set, the document field will also be set

docFields.name: audio
docFields.description: Optional. Message is an audio file, information about the file

docFields.name: document
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a general file, information about the file

docFields.name: photo
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a photo, available sizes of the photo

docFields.name: sticker
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a sticker, information about the sticker

docFields.name: story
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a forwarded story

docFields.name: video
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a video, information about the video

docFields.name: video_note
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a video note, information about the video message

docFields.name: voice
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a voice message, information about the file

docFields.name: caption
docFields.description: Optional. Caption for the animation, audio, document, photo, video or voice

docFields.name: caption_entities
docFields.description: Optional. For messages with a caption, special entities like usernames, URLs, bot commands, etc. that appear in the caption

docFields.name: show_caption_above_media
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the caption must be shown above the message media

docFields.name: has_media_spoiler
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the message media is covered by a spoiler animation

docFields.name: contact
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a shared contact, information about the contact

docFields.name: dice
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a dice with random value

docFields.name: game
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a game, information about the game. More about games »

docFields.name: poll
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a native poll, information about the poll

docFields.name: venue
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a venue, information about the venue. For backward compatibility, when this field is set, the location field will also be set

docFields.name: location
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a shared location, information about the location

docFields.name: new_chat_members
docFields.description: Optional. New members that were added to the group or supergroup and information about them (the bot itself may be one of these members)

docFields.name: left_chat_member
docFields.description: Optional. A member was removed from the group, information about them (this member may be the bot itself)

docFields.name: new_chat_title
docFields.description: Optional. A chat title was changed to this value

docFields.name: new_chat_photo
docFields.description: Optional. A chat photo was change to this value

docFields.description: Optional. Service message: the chat photo was deleted

docFields.name: group_chat_created
docFields.description: Optional. Service message: the group has been created

docFields.name: supergroup_chat_created
docFields.description: Optional. Service message: the supergroup has been created. This field can't be received in a message coming through updates, because bot can't be a member of a supergroup when it is created. It can only be found in reply_to_message if someone replies to a very first message in a directly created supergroup.

docFields.name: channel_chat_created
docFields.description: Optional. Service message: the channel has been created. This field can't be received in a message coming through updates, because bot can't be a member of a channel when it is created. It can only be found in reply_to_message if someone replies to a very first message in a channel.

docFields.name: message_auto_delete_timer_changed
docFields.description: Optional. Service message: auto-delete timer settings changed in the chat

docFields.name: migrate_to_chat_id
docFields.description: Optional. The group has been migrated to a supergroup with the specified identifier. This number may have more than 32 significant bits and some programming languages may have difficulty/silent defects in interpreting it. But it has at most 52 significant bits, so a signed 64-bit integer or double-precision float type are safe for storing this identifier.

docFields.name: migrate_from_chat_id
docFields.description: Optional. The supergroup has been migrated from a group with the specified identifier. This number may have more than 32 significant bits and some programming languages may have difficulty/silent defects in interpreting it. But it has at most 52 significant bits, so a signed 64-bit integer or double-precision float type are safe for storing this identifier.

docFields.name: pinned_message
docFields.description: Optional. Specified message was pinned. Note that the Message object in this field will not contain further reply_to_message fields even if it itself is a reply.

docTypes.name: MessageId
docTypes.description: This object represents a unique message identifier.

docFields.name: message_id
docFields.description: Unique message identifier

docTypes.name: InaccessibleMessage
docTypes.description: This object describes a message that was deleted or is otherwise inaccessible to the bot.

docFields.name: chat
docFields.description: Chat the message belonged to

docFields.name: message_id
docFields.description: Unique message identifier inside the chat

docFields.name: date
docFields.description: Always 0. The field can be used to differentiate regular and inaccessible messages.

docTypes.name: MessageEntity
docTypes.description: This object represents one special entity in a text message. For example, hashtags, usernames, URLs, etc.

docFields.name: type
docFields.description: Type of the entity. Currently, can be “mention” (@username), “hashtag” (#hashtag), “cashtag” ($USD), “bot_command” (/start@jobs_bot), “url” (https://telegram.org), “email” (do-not-reply@telegram.org), “phone_number” (+1-212-555-0123), “bold” (bold text), “italic” (italic text), “underline” (underlined text), “strikethrough” (strikethrough text), “spoiler” (spoiler message), “blockquote” (block quotation), “expandable_blockquote” (collapsed-by-default block quotation), “code” (monowidth string), “pre” (monowidth block), “text_link” (for clickable text URLs), “text_mention” (for users without usernames), “custom_emoji” (for inline custom emoji stickers)

docFields.name: offset
docFields.description: Offset in UTF-16 code units to the start of the entity

docFields.name: length
docFields.description: Length of the entity in UTF-16 code units

docFields.name: url
docFields.description: Optional. For “text_link” only, URL that will be opened after user taps on the text

docFields.name: user
docFields.description: Optional. For “text_mention” only, the mentioned user

docFields.name: language
docFields.description: Optional. For “pre” only, the programming language of the entity text

docFields.name: custom_emoji_id
docFields.description: Optional. For “custom_emoji” only, unique identifier of the custom emoji. Use getCustomEmojiStickers to get full information about the sticker

docTypes.name: TextQuote
docTypes.description: This object contains information about the quoted part of a message that is replied to by the given message.

docFields.name: text
docFields.description: Text of the quoted part of a message that is replied to by the given message

docFields.name: entities
docFields.description: Optional. Special entities that appear in the quote. Currently, only bold, italic, underline, strikethrough, spoiler, and custom_emoji entities are kept in quotes.

docFields.name: position
docFields.description: Approximate quote position in the original message in UTF-16 code units as specified by the sender

docFields.name: is_manual
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the quote was chosen manually by the message sender. Otherwise, the quote was added automatically by the server.

docTypes.name: ExternalReplyInfo

docFields.name: origin

docFields.name: chat
docFields.description: Optional. Chat the original message belongs to. Available only if the chat is a supergroup or a channel.

docFields.name: message_id
docFields.description: Optional. Unique message identifier inside the original chat. Available only if the original chat is a supergroup or a channel.

docFields.name: link_preview_options
docFields.description: Optional. Options used for link preview generation for the original message, if it is a text message

docFields.name: animation
docFields.description: Optional. Message is an animation, information about the animation

docFields.name: audio
docFields.description: Optional. Message is an audio file, information about the file

docFields.name: document
docFields.description: Optional. Message is a general file, information about the file

docFields.name: photo

docFields.name: sticker

docFields.name: invoice

docFields.name: venue

docTypes.name: ReplyParameters
docTypes.description: Describes reply parameters for the message that is being sent.

docFields.name: message_id
docFields.description: Identifier of the message that will be replied to in the current chat, or in the chat chat_id if it is specified

docFields.name: chat_id
docFields.description: Optional. If the message to be replied to is from a different chat, unique identifier for the chat or username of the channel (in the format @channelusername). Not supported for messages sent on behalf of a business account.

docFields.name: allow_sending_without_reply
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True if the message should be sent even if the specified message to be replied to is not found. Always False for replies in another chat or forum topic. Always True for messages sent on behalf of a business account.

docFields.name: quote
docFields.description: Optional. Quoted part of the message to be replied to; 0-1024 characters after entities parsing. The quote must be an exact substring of the message to be replied to, including bold, italic, underline, strikethrough, spoiler, and custom_emoji entities. The message will fail to send if the quote isn't found in the original message.

docFields.name: quote_parse_mode
docFields.description: Optional. Mode for parsing entities in the quote. See formatting options for more details.

docFields.name: quote_entities
docFields.description: Optional. A JSON-serialized list of special entities that appear in the quote. It can be specified instead of quote_parse_mode.

docFields.name: quote_position
docFields.description: Optional. Position of the quote in the original message in UTF-16 code units

docFields.name: fill
docFields.description: The background fill

docFields.name: dark_theme_dimming

docTypes.name: BackgroundTypeWallpaper

docFields.name: document

docFields.name: dark_theme_dimming

docFields.name: is_blurred

docFields.name: is_moving

docTypes.name: BackgroundTypePattern
docTypes.description: The background is a PNG or TGV (gzipped subset of SVG with MIME type “application/x-tgwallpattern”) pattern to be combined with the background fill chosen by the user.

docFields.name: type

docFields.name: fill

docFields.name: intensity

docFields.name: is_inverted

docFields.name: is_moving

docTypes.name: BackgroundTypeChatTheme

docFields.name: icon_custom_emoji_id

docTypes.name: SharedUser
docTypes.description: This object contains information about a user that was shared with the bot using a KeyboardButtonRequestUsers button.

docFields.name: user_id
docFields.description: Identifier of the shared user. This number may have more than 32 significant bits and some programming languages may have difficulty/silent defects in interpreting it. But it has at most 52 significant bits, so 64-bit integers or double-precision float types are safe for storing these identifiers. The bot may not have access to the user and could be unable to use this identifier, unless the user is already known to the bot by some other means.

docFields.name: first_name
docFields.description: Optional. First name of the user, if the name was requested by the bot

docFields.name: last_name
docFields.description: Optional. Last name of the user, if the name was requested by the bot

docFields.name: username

docFields.name: photo
docFields.description: Optional. Available sizes of the chat photo, if the photo was requested by the bot

docTypes.name: UsersShared
docTypes.description: This object contains information about the users whose identifiers were shared with the bot using a KeyboardButtonRequestUsers button.

docFields.name: request_id
docFields.description: Identifier of the request

docFields.name: users
docFields.description: Information about users shared with the bot.

docTypes.name: ChatShared
docTypes.description: This object contains information about a chat that was shared with the bot using a KeyboardButtonRequestChat button.

docFields.name: request_id
docFields.description: Identifier of the request

docFields.name: chat_id
docFields.description: Identifier of the shared chat. This number may have more than 32 significant bits and some programming languages may have difficulty/silent defects in interpreting it. But it has at most 52 significant bits, so a 64-bit integer or double-precision float type are safe for storing this identifier. The bot may not have access to the chat and could be unable to use this identifier, unless the chat is already known to the bot by some other means.

docFields.name: title
docFields.description: Optional. Title of the chat, if the title was requested by the bot.

docFields.name: username
docFields.description: Optional. Username of the chat, if the username was requested by the bot and available.

docFields.name: photo
docFields.description: Optional. Available sizes of the chat photo, if the photo was requested by the bot

docTypes.name: WriteAccessAllowed
docTypes.description: This object represents a service message about a user allowing a bot to write messages after adding it to the attachment menu, launching a Web App from a link, or accepting an explicit request from a Web App sent by the method requestWriteAccess.

docFields.name: from_request
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the access was granted after the user accepted an explicit request from a Web App sent by the method requestWriteAccess

docFields.name: web_app_name
docFields.description: Optional. Name of the Web App, if the access was granted when the Web App was launched from a link

docFields.name: from_attachment_menu
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the access was granted when the bot was added to the attachment or side menu

docTypes.name: VideoChatScheduled
docTypes.description: This object represents a service message about a video chat scheduled in the chat.

docFields.name: start_date
docFields.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the video chat is supposed to be started by a chat administrator

docTypes.name: VideoChatEnded
docTypes.description: This object represents a service message about a video chat ended in the chat.

docFields.name: duration
docFields.description: Video chat duration in seconds

docTypes.name: VideoChatParticipantsInvited
docTypes.description: This object represents a service message about new members invited to a video chat.

docFields.name: users
docFields.description: New members that were invited to the video chat

docTypes.name: Giveaway
docTypes.description: This object represents a message about a scheduled giveaway.

docFields.name: chats
docFields.description: The list of chats which the user must join to participate in the giveaway

docFields.name: winners_selection_date
docFields.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when winners of the giveaway will be selected

docFields.name: winner_count
docFields.description: The number of users which are supposed to be selected as winners of the giveaway

docFields.name: only_new_members
docFields.description: Optional. True, if only users who join the chats after the giveaway started should be eligible to win

docFields.name: has_public_winners
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the list of giveaway winners will be visible to everyone

docFields.name: prize_description
docFields.description: Optional. Description of additional giveaway prize

docFields.name: country_codes
docFields.description: Optional. A list of two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country codes indicating the countries from which eligible users for the giveaway must come. If empty, then all users can participate in the giveaway. Users with a phone number that was bought on Fragment can always participate in giveaways.

docFields.name: premium_subscription_month_count
docFields.description: Optional. The number of months the Telegram Premium subscription won from the giveaway will be active for

docTypes.name: GiveawayWinners
docTypes.description: This object represents a message about the completion of a giveaway with public winners.

docFields.name: chat
docFields.description: The chat that created the giveaway

docFields.name: giveaway_message_id
docFields.description: Identifier of the message with the giveaway in the chat

docFields.name: winners_selection_date
docFields.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when winners of the giveaway were selected

docFields.name: winner_count
docFields.description: Total number of winners in the giveaway

docFields.name: winners
docFields.description: List of up to 100 winners of the giveaway

docFields.name: additional_chat_count
docFields.description: Optional. The number of other chats the user had to join in order to be eligible for the giveaway

docFields.name: premium_subscription_month_count
docFields.description: Optional. The number of months the Telegram Premium subscription won from the giveaway will be active for

docFields.name: unclaimed_prize_count
docFields.description: Optional. Number of undistributed prizes

docFields.name: only_new_members
docFields.description: Optional. True, if only users who had joined the chats after the giveaway started were eligible to win

docFields.name: was_refunded
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the giveaway was canceled because the payment for it was refunded

docFields.name: prize_description

docTypes.name: LinkPreviewOptions
docTypes.description: Describes the options used for link preview generation.

docFields.name: is_disabled
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the link preview is disabled

docFields.name: url
docFields.description: Optional. URL to use for the link preview. If empty, then the first URL found in the message text will be used

docFields.name: prefer_small_media
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the media in the link preview is supposed to be shrunk; ignored if the URL isn't explicitly specified or media size change isn't supported for the preview

docFields.name: prefer_large_media
docFields.description: Optional. True, if the media in the link preview is supposed to be enlarged; ignored if the URL isn't explicitly specified or media size change isn't supported for the preview

docFields.name: show_above_text

docTypes.name: UserProfilePhotos

docFields.name: total_count
docFields.description: Total number of profile pictures the target user has

docFields.name: photos
docFields.description: Requested profile pictures (in up to 4 sizes each)

docTypes.name: File
docTypes.description:
This object represents a file ready to be downloaded. The file can be downloaded via the link https://api.telegram.org/file/bot<token>/<file_path>. It is guaranteed that the link will be valid for at least 1 hour. When the link expires, a new one can be requested by calling getFile.

The maximum file size to download is 20 MB

docFields.name: file_id
docFields.description: Identifier for this file, which can be used to download or reuse the file

docFields.name: file_unique_id
docFields.description: Unique identifier for this file, which is supposed to be the same over time and for different bots. Can't be used to download or reuse the file.

docFields.name: file_size
docFields.description: Optional. File size in bytes. It can be bigger than 2^31 and some programming languages may have difficulty/silent defects in interpreting it. But it has at most 52 significant bits, so a signed 64-bit integer or double-precision float type are safe for storing this value.

docFields.name: file_path
docFields.description: Optional. File path. Use https://api.telegram.org/file/bot<token>/<file_path> to get the file.

docTypes.name: WebAppInfo
docTypes.description: Describes a Web App.

docFields.name: url
docFields.description: An HTTPS URL of a Web App to be opened with additional data as specified in Initializing Web Apps

docTypes.name: ReplyKeyboardMarkup
docTypes.description: This object represents a custom keyboard with reply options (see Introduction to bots for details and examples). Not supported in channels and for messages sent on behalf of a Telegram Business account.

docFields.name: keyboard
docFields.description: Array of button rows, each represented by an Array of KeyboardButton objects

docFields.name: is_persistent
docFields.description: Optional. Requests clients to always show the keyboard when the regular keyboard is hidden. Defaults to false, in which case the custom keyboard can be hidden and opened with a keyboard icon.

docFields.name: resize_keyboard
docFields.description: Optional. Requests clients to resize the keyboard vertically for optimal fit (e.g., make the keyboard smaller if there are just two rows of buttons). Defaults to false, in which case the custom keyboard is always of the same height as the app's standard keyboard.

docFields.name: one_time_keyboard
docFields.description: Optional. Requests clients to hide the keyboard as soon as it's been used. The keyboard will still be available, but clients will automatically display the usual letter-keyboard in the chat - the user can press a special button in the input field to see the custom keyboard again. Defaults to false.

docFields.name: input_field_placeholder
docFields.description: Optional. The placeholder to be shown in the input field when the keyboard is active; 1-64 characters

docFields.name: selective
docFields.description:
Optional. Use this parameter if you want to show the keyboard to specific users only. Targets: 1) users that are @mentioned in the text of the Message object; 2) if the bot's message is a reply to a message in the same chat and forum topic, sender of the original message.

Example: A user requests to change the bot's language, bot replies to the request with a keyboard to select the new language. Other users in the group don't see the keyboard.

docTypes.name: KeyboardButton
docTypes.description:
This object represents one button of the reply keyboard. At most one of the optional fields must be used to specify type of the button. For simple text buttons, String can be used instead of this object to specify the button text.

Note: request_users and request_chat options will only work in Telegram versions released after 3 February, 2023. Older clients will display unsupported message.

docFields.name: text
docFields.description: Text of the button. If none of the optional fields are used, it will be sent as a message when the button is pressed

docFields.name: request_users
docFields.description: Optional. If specified, pressing the button will open a list of suitable users. Identifiers of selected users will be sent to the bot in a “users_shared” service message. Available in private chats only.

docFields.name: request_chat
docFields.description: Optional. If specified, pressing the button will open a list of suitable chats. Tapping on a chat will send its identifier to the bot in a “chat_shared” service message. Available in private chats only.

docFields.name: request_contact
docFields.description: Optional. If True, the user's phone number will be sent as a contact when the button is pressed. Available in private chats only.

docFields.name: request_location
docFields.description: Optional. If True, the user's current location will be sent when the button is pressed. Available in private chats only.

docFields.name: request_poll
docFields.description: Optional. If specified, the user will be asked to create a poll and send it to the bot when the button is pressed. Available in private chats only.

docFields.name: web_app
docFields.description: Optional. If specified, the described Web App will be launched when the button is pressed. The Web App will be able to send a “web_app_data” service message. Available in private chats only.

docTypes.name: KeyboardButtonRequestUsers
docTypes.description: This object defines the criteria used to request suitable users. Information about the selected users will be shared with the bot when the corresponding button is pressed. More about requesting users »

docFields.name: request_id
docFields.description: Signed 32-bit identifier of the request that will be received back in the UsersShared object. Must be unique within the message

docFields.name: user_is_bot
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request bots, pass False to request regular users. If not specified, no additional restrictions are applied.

docFields.name: user_is_premium
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request premium users, pass False to request non-premium users. If not specified, no additional restrictions are applied.

docFields.name: max_quantity
docFields.description: Optional. The maximum number of users to be selected; 1-10. Defaults to 1.

docFields.name: request_name
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request the users' first and last names

docFields.name: request_username
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request the users' usernames

docFields.name: request_photo
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request the users' photos

docTypes.name: KeyboardButtonRequestChat
docTypes.description: This object defines the criteria used to request a suitable chat. Information about the selected chat will be shared with the bot when the corresponding button is pressed. The bot will be granted requested rights in the chat if appropriate. More about requesting chats ».

docFields.name: request_id
docFields.description: Signed 32-bit identifier of the request, which will be received back in the ChatShared object. Must be unique within the message

docFields.name: chat_is_channel
docFields.description: Pass True to request a channel chat, pass False to request a group or a supergroup chat.

docFields.name: chat_is_forum
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request a forum supergroup, pass False to request a non-forum chat. If not specified, no additional restrictions are applied.

docFields.name: chat_has_username
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request a supergroup or a channel with a username, pass False to request a chat without a username. If not specified, no additional restrictions are applied.

docFields.name: chat_is_created
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request a chat owned by the user. Otherwise, no additional restrictions are applied.

docFields.name: user_administrator_rights
docFields.description: Optional. A JSON-serialized object listing the required administrator rights of the user in the chat. The rights must be a superset of bot_administrator_rights. If not specified, no additional restrictions are applied.

docFields.name: bot_administrator_rights
docFields.description: Optional. A JSON-serialized object listing the required administrator rights of the bot in the chat. The rights must be a subset of user_administrator_rights. If not specified, no additional restrictions are applied.

docFields.name: bot_is_member
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request a chat with the bot as a member. Otherwise, no additional restrictions are applied.

docFields.name: request_title
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request the chat's title

docFields.name: request_username
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request the chat's username

docFields.name: request_photo
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request the chat's photo

docTypes.name: KeyboardButtonPollType
docTypes.description: This object represents type of a poll, which is allowed to be created and sent when the corresponding button is pressed.

docFields.name: type
docFields.description: Optional. If quiz is passed, the user will be allowed to create only polls in the quiz mode. If regular is passed, only regular polls will be allowed. Otherwise, the user will be allowed to create a poll of any type.

docTypes.name: ReplyKeyboardRemove
docTypes.description: Upon receiving a message with this object, Telegram clients will remove the current custom keyboard and display the default letter-keyboard. By default, custom keyboards are displayed until a new keyboard is sent by a bot. An exception is made for one-time keyboards that are hidden immediately after the user presses a button (see ReplyKeyboardMarkup). Not supported in channels and for messages sent on behalf of a Telegram Business account.

docFields.name: remove_keyboard
docFields.description: Requests clients to remove the custom keyboard (user will not be able to summon this keyboard; if you want to hide the keyboard from sight but keep it accessible, use one_time_keyboard in ReplyKeyboardMarkup)

docFields.name: selective
docFields.description:
Optional. Use this parameter if you want to remove the keyboard for specific users only. Targets: 1) users that are @mentioned in the text of the Message object; 2) if the bot's message is a reply to a message in the same chat and forum topic, sender of the original message.

Example: A user votes in a poll, bot returns confirmation message in reply to the vote and removes the keyboard for that user, while still showing the keyboard with poll options to users who haven't voted yet.

docTypes.name: InlineKeyboardMarkup
docTypes.description: This object represents an inline keyboard that appears right next to the message it belongs to.

docFields.name: inline_keyboard
docFields.description: Array of button rows, each represented by an Array of InlineKeyboardButton objects

docTypes.name: InlineKeyboardButton
docTypes.description: This object represents one button of an inline keyboard. Exactly one of the optional fields must be used to specify type of the button.

docFields.name: text
docFields.description: Label text on the button

docFields.name: url
docFields.description: Optional. HTTP or tg:// URL to be opened when the button is pressed. Links tg://user?id=<user_id> can be used to mention a user by their identifier without using a username, if this is allowed by their privacy settings.

docFields.name: callback_data
docFields.description: Optional. Data to be sent in a callback query to the bot when button is pressed, 1-64 bytes. Not supported for messages sent on behalf of a Telegram Business account.

docFields.name: web_app
docFields.description: Optional. Description of the Web App that will be launched when the user presses the button. The Web App will be able to send an arbitrary message on behalf of the user using the method answerWebAppQuery. Available only in private chats between a user and the bot. Not supported for messages sent on behalf of a Telegram Business account.

docFields.name: login_url
docFields.description: Optional. An HTTPS URL used to automatically authorize the user. Can be used as a replacement for the Telegram Login Widget.

docFields.name: switch_inline_query
docFields.description: Optional. If set, pressing the button will prompt the user to select one of their chats, open that chat and insert the bot's username and the specified inline query in the input field. May be empty, in which case just the bot's username will be inserted. Not supported for messages sent on behalf of a Telegram Business account.

docFields.name: switch_inline_query_current_chat
docFields.description:
Optional. If set, pressing the button will insert the bot's username and the specified inline query in the current chat's input field. May be empty, in which case only the bot's username will be inserted.

This offers a quick way for the user to open your bot in inline mode in the same chat - good for selecting something from multiple options. Not supported in channels and for messages sent on behalf of a Telegram Business account.

docFields.name: switch_inline_query_chosen_chat
docFields.description: Optional. If set, pressing the button will prompt the user to select one of their chats of the specified type, open that chat and insert the bot's username and the specified inline query in the input field. Not supported for messages sent on behalf of a Telegram Business account.

docFields.name: callback_game
docFields.description:
Optional. Description of the game that will be launched when the user presses the button.

NOTE: This type of button must always be the first button in the first row.

docFields.name: pay
docFields.description:
Optional. Specify True, to send a Pay button. Substrings “” and “XTR” in the buttons's text will be replaced with a Telegram Star icon.

NOTE: This type of button must always be the first button in the first row and can only be used in invoice messages.

docTypes.name: LoginUrl
docTypes.description:
This object represents a parameter of the inline keyboard button used to automatically authorize a user. Serves as a great replacement for the Telegram Login Widget when the user is coming from Telegram. All the user needs to do is tap/click a button and confirm that they want to log in:

Telegram apps support these buttons as of version 5.7.

Sample bot: @discussbot

docFields.name: url
docFields.description:
An HTTPS URL to be opened with user authorization data added to the query string when the button is pressed. If the user refuses to provide authorization data, the original URL without information about the user will be opened. The data added is the same as described in Receiving authorization data.

NOTE: You must always check the hash of the received data to verify the authentication and the integrity of the data as described in Checking authorization.

docFields.name: forward_text
docFields.description: Optional. New text of the button in forwarded messages.

docFields.name: bot_username
docFields.description: Optional. Username of a bot, which will be used for user authorization. See Setting up a bot for more details. If not specified, the current bot's username will be assumed. The url's domain must be the same as the domain linked with the bot. See Linking your domain to the bot for more details.

docFields.name: request_write_access
docFields.description: Optional. Pass True to request the permission for your bot to send messages to the user.

docTypes.name: SwitchInlineQueryChosenChat
docTypes.description: This object represents an inline button that switches the current user to inline mode in a chosen chat, with an optional default inline query.

docFields.name: query
docFields.description: Optional. The default inline query to be inserted in the input field. If left empty, only the bot's username will be inserted

docFields.name: allow_user_chats
docFields.description: Optional. True, if private chats with users can be chosen

docFields.name: allow_bot_chats
docFields.description: Optional. True, if private chats with bots can be chosen

docFields.name: allow_group_chats
docFields.description: Optional. True, if group and supergroup chats can be chosen

docFields.name: allow_channel_chats
docFields.description: Optional. True, if channel chats can be chosen

docTypes.name: CallbackQuery
docTypes.description:
This object represents an incoming callback query from a callback button in an inline keyboard. If the button that originated the query was attached to a message sent by the bot, the field message will be present. If the button was attached to a message sent via the bot (in inline mode), the field inline_message_id will be present. Exactly one of the fields data or game_short_name will be present.

NOTE: After the user presses a callback button, Telegram clients will display a progress bar until you call answerCallbackQuery. It is, therefore, necessary to react by calling answerCallbackQuery even if no notification to the user is needed (e.g., without specifying any of the optional parameters).

docFields.name: id
docFields.description: Unique identifier for this query

docFields.name: from
docFields.description: Sender

docFields.name: message
docFields.description: Optional. Message sent by the bot with the callback button that originated the query

docFields.name: inline_message_id
docFields.description: Optional. Identifier of the message sent via the bot in inline mode, that originated the query.

docFields.name: chat_instance
docFields.description: Global identifier, uniquely corresponding to the chat to which the message with the callback button was sent. Useful for high scores in games.

docFields.name: data
docFields.description: Optional. Data associated with the callback button. Be aware that the message originated the query can contain no callback buttons with this data.

docFields.name: game_short_name
docFields.description: Optional. Short name of a Game to be returned, serves as the unique identifier for the game

docTypes.name: ForceReply
docTypes.description:
Upon receiving a message with this object, Telegram clients will display a reply interface to the user (act as if the user has selected the bot's message and tapped 'Reply'). This can be extremely useful if you want to create user-friendly step-by-step interfaces without having to sacrifice privacy mode. Not supported in channels and for messages sent on behalf of a Telegram Business account.

Example: A poll bot for groups runs in privacy mode (only receives commands, replies to its messages and mentions). There could be two ways to create a new poll:

  • Explain the user how to send a command with parameters (e.g. /newpoll question answer1 answer2). May be appealing for hardcore users but lacks modern day polish.
  • Guide the user through a step-by-step process. 'Please send me your question', 'Cool, now let's add the first answer option', 'Great. Keep adding answer options, then send /done when you're ready'.

The last option is definitely more attractive. And if you use ForceReply in your bot's questions, it will receive the user's answers even if it only receives replies, commands and mentions - without any extra work for the user.

docFields.name: force_reply
docFields.description: Shows reply interface to the user, as if they manually selected the bot's message and tapped 'Reply'

docFields.name: input_field_placeholder
docFields.description: Optional. The placeholder to be shown in the input field when the reply is active; 1-64 characters

docFields.name: selective
docFields.description: Optional. Use this parameter if you want to force reply from specific users only. Targets: 1) users that are @mentioned in the text of the Message object; 2) if the bot's message is a reply to a message in the same chat and forum topic, sender of the original message.

docTypes.name: ChatPhoto
docTypes.description: This object represents a chat photo.

docFields.name: small_file_id
docFields.description: File identifier of small (160x160) chat photo. This file_id can be used only for photo download and only for as long as the photo is not changed.

docFields.name: small_file_unique_id
docFields.description: Unique file identifier of small (160x160) chat photo, which is supposed to be the same over time and for different bots. Can't be used to download or reuse the file.

docFields.name: big_file_id
docFields.description: File identifier of big (640x640) chat photo. This file_id can be used only for photo download and only for as long as the photo is not changed.

docFields.name: big_file_unique_id
docFields.description: Unique file identifier of big (640x640) chat photo, which is supposed to be the same over time and for different bots. Can't be used to download or reuse the file.

docTypes.name: ChatInviteLink
docTypes.description: Represents an invite link for a chat.

docFields.name: invite_link

More information on Sending Files »

docFields.name: thumbnail
docFields.description: Optional. Thumbnail of the file sent; can be ignored if thumbnail generation for the file is supported server-side. The thumbnail should be in JPEG format and less than 200 kB in size. A thumbnail's width and height should not exceed 320. Ignored if the file is not uploaded using multipart/form-data. Thumbnails can't be reused and can be only uploaded as a new file, so you can pass “attach://<file_attach_name>” if the thumbnail was uploaded using multipart/form-data under <file_attach_name>. name: Available methods
description:
All methods in the Bot API are case-insensitive. We support GET and POST HTTP methods. Use either URL query string or application/json or application/x-www-form-urlencoded or multipart/form-data for passing parameters in Bot API requests.
On successful call, a JSON-object containing the result will be returned.

docMethods.name: logOut
docMethods.description: Use this method to log out from the cloud Bot API server before launching the bot locally. You must log out the bot before running it locally, otherwise there is no guarantee that the bot will receive updates. After a successful call, you can immediately log in on a local server, but will not be able to log in back to the cloud Bot API server for 10 minutes. Returns True on success. Requires no parameters.

docMethods.name: close
docMethods.description: Use this method to close the bot instance before moving it from one local server to another. You need to delete the webhook before calling this method to ensure that the bot isn't launched again after server restart. The method will return error 429 in the first 10 minutes after the bot is launched. Returns True on success. Requires no parameters.

docMethods.name: sendChatAction
docMethods.description:
Use this method when you need to tell the user that something is happening on the bot's side. The status is set for 5 seconds or less (when a message arrives from your bot, Telegram clients clear its typing status). Returns True on success.

Example: The ImageBot needs some time to process a request and upload the image. Instead of sending a text message along the lines of “Retrieving image, please wait…”, the bot may use sendChatAction with action = upload_photo. The user will see a “sending photo” status for the bot.

We only recommend using this method when a response from the bot will take a noticeable amount of time to arrive.

docParameters.name: business_connection_id
docParameters.description: Unique identifier of the business connection on behalf of which the action will be sent

docParameters.name: chat_id
docParameters.description: Unique identifier for the target chat or username of the target channel (in the format @channelusername)

docParameters.name: message_thread_id
docParameters.description: Unique identifier for the target message thread; for supergroups only

docParameters.name: action
docParameters.description: Type of action to broadcast. Choose one, depending on what the user is about to receive: typing for text messages, upload_photo for photos, record_video or upload_video for videos, record_voice or upload_voice for voice notes, upload_document for general files, choose_sticker for stickers, find_location for location data, record_video_note or upload_video_note for video notes.

docParametersSorded.description: Unique identifier for the target chat or username of the target channel (in the format @channelusername)

docMethods.name: getFile
docMethods.description:
Use this method to get basic information about a file and prepare it for downloading. For the moment, bots can download files of up to 20MB in size. On success, a File object is returned. The file can then be downloaded via the link https://api.telegram.org/file/bot<token>/<file_path>, where <file_path> is taken from the response. It is guaranteed that the link will be valid for at least 1 hour. When the link expires, a new one can be requested by calling getFile again.

Note: This function may not preserve the original file name and MIME type. You should save the file's MIME type and name (if available) when the File object is received.

docParameters.name: file_id
docParameters.description: File identifier to get information about

docParametersSorded.name: file_id
docParametersSorded.description: File identifier to get information about

docMethods.name: banChatMember
docMethods.description: Use this method to ban a user in a group, a supergroup or a channel. In the case of supergroups and channels, the user will not be able to return to the chat on their own using invite links, etc., unless unbanned first. The bot must be an administrator in the chat for this to work and must have the appropriate administrator rights. Returns True on success.

docParameters.name: chat_id
docParameters.description: Unique identifier for the target group or username of the target supergroup or channel (in the format @channelusername)

docParameters.name: user_id
docParameters.description: Unique identifier of the target user

docParameters.name: until_date
docParameters.description: Date when the user will be unbanned; Unix time. If user is banned for more than 366 days or less than 30 seconds from the current time they are considered to be banned forever. Applied for supergroups and channels only.

docParameters.name: revoke_messages
docParameters.description: Pass True to delete all messages from the chat for the user that is being removed. If False, the user will be able to see messages in the group that were sent before the user was removed. Always True for supergroups and channels.

docParametersSorded.description: Unique identifier for the target group or username of the target supergroup or channel (in the format @channelusername)

docParametersSorded.name: user_id
docParametersSorded.description: Unique identifier of the target user

docParametersSorded.name: until_date
docParametersSorded.description: Date when the user will be unbanned; Unix time. If user is banned for more than 366 days or less than 30 seconds from the current time they are considered to be banned forever. Applied for supergroups and channels only.

docParametersSorded.name: revoke_messages
docParametersSorded.description: Pass True to delete all messages from the chat for the user that is being removed. If False, the user will be able to see messages in the group that were sent before the user was removed. Always True for supergroups and channels.

docMethods.name: unbanChatMember
docMethods.description: Use this method to unban a previously banned user in a supergroup or channel. The user will not return to the group or channel automatically, but will be able to join via link, etc. The bot must be an administrator for this to work. By default, this method guarantees that after the call the user is not a member of the chat, but will be able to join it. So if the user is a member of the chat they will also be removed from the chat. If you don't want this, use the parameter only_if_banned. Returns True on success.

docParameters.name: chat_id
docParameters.description: Unique identifier for the target group or username of the target supergroup or channel (in the format @channelusername)

docParameters.name: user_id
docParameters.description: Unique identifier of the target user

docParameters.name: only_if_banned
docParameters.description: Do nothing if the user is not banned

docMethods.description: Use this method to restrict a user in a supergroup. The bot must be an administrator in the supergroup for this to work and must have the appropriate administrator rights. Pass True for all permissions to lift restrictions from a user. Returns True on success.

docParameters.name: chat_id
docParameters.description: Unique identifier for the target chat or username of the target supergroup (in the format @supergroupusername)

docParameters.name: user_id
docParameters.description: Unique identifier of the target user

docParameters.description: A JSON-serialized object for new user permissions

docParameters.name: use_independent_chat_permissions
docParameters.description: Pass True if chat permissions are set independently. Otherwise, the can_send_other_messages and can_add_web_page_previews permissions will imply the can_send_messages, can_send_audios, can_send_documents, can_send_photos, can_send_videos, can_send_video_notes, and can_send_voice_notes permissions; the can_send_polls permission will imply the can_send_messages permission.

docParameters.name: until_date
docParameters.description: Date when restrictions will be lifted for the user; Unix time. If user is restricted for more than 366 days or less than 30 seconds from the current time, they are considered to be restricted forever

docMethods.name: exportChatInviteLink
docMethods.description:
Use this method to generate a new primary invite link for a chat; any previously generated primary link is revoked. The bot must be an administrator in the chat for this to work and must have the appropriate administrator rights. Returns the new invite link as String on success.

Note: Each administrator in a chat generates their own invite links. Bots can't use invite links generated by other administrators. If you want your bot to work with invite links, it will need to generate its own link using exportChatInviteLink or by calling the getChat method. If your bot needs to generate a new primary invite link replacing its previous one, use exportChatInviteLink again.
